## Quick orientation

This is an hexagonal architecture with a strict package dependency chain:

```text
@efesto-cloud/* (shared libraries — Entity, Maybe, Result, Population, MongoDBContext, …)
    ↓
{{ns}}/core       domain model + use cases (ports)
    ↓
{{#if has_mongodb}}{{ns}}/mongodb    MongoDB adapter (repo implementations)
    ↓
{{/if}}{{#if has_webapp}}{{ns}}/webapp     React Router 7 admin application
{{/if}}```

## Where to work

| Task | Navigate to | Specialized skill |
|---|---|---|
| Add an entity / DTO / value object / enum / type / error / dict | `packages/core/src/` | `entity`, `value-object`, `type-enum-dict` |
| Add a use case or service port | `packages/core/src/useCase/`, `packages/core/src/service/` | `usecase` |
{{#if has_mongodb}}| Add a MongoDB repository or mapper | `packages/mongodb/src/` | `persistence`, `population` |
{{/if}}{{#if has_webapp}}| Add a React Router route / loader / action | `packages/webapp/app/routes/` | `webapp-loader-action` |
| Build UI components | `packages/webapp/app/components/` | `daisyui` |
{{/if}}

## Conventions

- **pnpm** workspaces (not npm/yarn).
- **Biome** for lint/format (not ESLint/Prettier). 4-space indent, double quotes.
- **TypeScript** strict mode with `~/*` → `./src/*` alias.
- **Always use `.js` extension in imports**, even for `.ts` files — `nodenext` + `tsc-alias` require it.
- **Inversify** for DI. Hierarchical `Symbols` registry.
- **Result / Maybe** for error handling (never throw).
- **Soft-delete** via `entity.delete()` + `repo.save()` — never `repo.delete()`.
- **Locale**: {{locale}}. **Timezone**: {{timezone}}.

## Common commands

```bash
pnpm install                 # install everything
pnpm -r build                # build all packages
pnpm -r typecheck            # type-check all packages
pnpm biome                   # lint + format
{{#if has_webapp}}cd packages/webapp && pnpm dev   # start the admin
{{/if}}```

